## Goal

Convert Employee from Mongo `@Document` to JPA `@Entity` with `@TenantId` discriminator.

### `Employee.java` (modify in place)

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = \"employees\")
public class Employee {
    @Id
    private UUID id;

    @TenantId
    @Column(name = \"organization_id\")
    private UUID organizationId;

    @Column(nullable = false)
    private String name;

    // other fields per V1 schema...

    // getters/setters
}
```

- `@Id UUID` — drop Counter-generated long.
- `@TenantId @Column(name=\"organization_id\")` — Hibernate auto-populates on insert from `CurrentTenantIdentifierResolver`; auto-filters on load.
- Fields match V1 schema's `employees` table columns.
- Remove Mongo imports (`@Document`, etc.).

### `EmployeeRepository.java` (modify)

```java
public interface EmployeeRepository extends JpaRepository<Employee, UUID> {
    List<Employee> findByNameContainingIgnoreCase(String name);
    Page<Employee> findAll(Pageable pageable);  // inherited; preserve usage
}
```

- `JpaRepository<Employee, UUID>` — generic args change.
- `findByNameContainingIgnoreCase` — Spring Data derived query; semantically equivalent to Mongo regex contains (per `docs/reference/lessons.md`).

### Why each decision

- **`@TenantId` annotation placement**: on the field, not the column — Hibernate 6 idiom.
- **No `@Filter` annotation**: rejected design; `@TenantId` is the replacement.
- **`containsIgnoreCase`**: preserves search semantics from Mongo (`docs/reference/lessons.md` — search is partial/case-insensitive everywhere).

### Dependencies

Slice 3 (S3_GREEN). Verifies the @TenantId plumbing works.

### Verification

- `./mvnw compile` clean.
- `EmployeeRepositoryIntegrationTest`'s @TenantId tests (S4_RED) pass — proves discriminator engages on save() and find*().

### Considerations

- If Employee has a `phoneNumber` field, it's NOT subject to the per-org uniqueness (that's Client). Schema-driven.
- Don't add `@TenantId` to the `id` field — only the organizationId field is the discriminator.
- Field-level vs property-level access: match existing Spring conventions in the codebase (typically field-level with Lombok).

## Goal

Port Appointment domain to JPA. Model the junction table with explicit @Entity + @EmbeddedId (NOT @ManyToMany — composite FK enforcement requires it).

### `Appointment.java` (modify)

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = \"appointments\")
public class Appointment {
    @Id private UUID id;
    @TenantId @Column(name = \"organization_id\") private UUID organizationId;
    @Column(name = \"starts_at\", nullable = false) private OffsetDateTime startsAt;
    @Column(name = \"ends_at\", nullable = false) private OffsetDateTime endsAt;
    @Column(name = \"customer_name\", nullable = false) private String customerName;
    @Column(name = \"phone_number\") private String phoneNumber;
    private UUID employeeId;
    private UUID clientId;  // nullable
    @Column(name = \"showed_up\") private Boolean showedUp;
    @Column(name = \"reminder_sent_at\") private OffsetDateTime reminderSentAt;
    @Column(name = \"archived_at\") private OffsetDateTime archivedAt;
    // ... per V1 schema
}
```

### `AppointmentServiceLink.java` (new)

```java
@Entity
@Table(name = \"appointment_services\")
public class AppointmentServiceLink {
    @EmbeddedId private AppointmentServiceLinkId id;
    @TenantId @Column(name = \"organization_id\") private UUID organizationId;
    // ...
}

@Embeddable
public class AppointmentServiceLinkId implements Serializable {
    @Column(name = \"appointment_id\") private UUID appointmentId;
    @Column(name = \"service_id\") private UUID serviceId;
}
```

### `AppointmentRepository.java`

```java
public interface AppointmentRepository extends JpaRepository<Appointment, UUID> {
    List<Appointment> findByStartsAtBetween(OffsetDateTime start, OffsetDateTime end);
    List<Appointment> findByPhoneNumberContaining(String phone);
    List<Appointment> findByEmployeeIdAndStartsAtBetween(UUID employeeId, OffsetDateTime start, OffsetDateTime end);
    // ... plus archived filter as derived or via @Where
}
```

### Why explicit @Entity + @EmbeddedId on the junction

Plan calls this out as MANDATORY: 'Hibernate `@ManyToMany` with `@JoinTable` cannot populate a non-key column on the junction, so the composite-FK enforcement makes the explicit-entity path mandatory.'

The V1 schema's `appointment_services.organization_id` participates in composite FKs to both `appointments(id, organization_id)` AND `services(id, organization_id)`. Without populating it on the junction, the link insert fails the FK check.

Cascade-on-delete for the appointment-side relationship relies on the schema's `ON DELETE CASCADE`.

### archived_at handling

V1 schema has NO separate `archived_appointments` table. `archived_at` on the SINGLE `appointments` table is the soft-delete marker. List endpoints filter `archived_at IS NULL` by default.

### Dependencies

Slices 4 (Employees), 5 (Services), 6 (Clients) — Appointment references all three by FK.

### Verification

- Slice 7 backend tests (S7_RED_BE) for repo + entity start passing.
- @TenantId @EmbeddedId discriminator test in S7_RED_BE passes — closes the deferred-from-U3 gate.

### Considerations

- `OffsetDateTime` chosen for the timestamp type (per Key Technical Decisions): maps to `timestamptz` cleanly; Jackson serializes to ISO 8601 with offset by default; preserves offset metadata for the frontend. NOT `Instant` (discards offset) or `ZonedDateTime` (adds zone name we don't carry).
- AppointmentServiceLinkId must implement Serializable (Hibernate composite-PK contract).

## Goal

Controller wiring + SMS scheduler refactor + the Phase 2 exit gate test.

### `AppointmentController.java`

- `@PathVariable UUID id`.
- Request body uses `startsAt`/`endsAt` (not `date`/`startTime`/`endTime`).
- `GET /appointments/date/{YYYY-MM-DD}` accepts a `LocalDate` path var, calls `getAppointmentsByDate(date)` which uses org tz.
- 409 on conflict with body `{description: \"<msg>\"}` — must match AppointmentModal's `err.response.data.description` reader.
- 400 on validation/CHECK constraint failures with field map.

### `SmsService.java` refactor

**`sendReminders()` new shape (iterate-orgs-loop pattern):**

```java
@Scheduled(cron = \"0 0 15 * * *\", zone = \"America/New_York\")
public void sendReminders() {
    List<UUID> orgIds = findOrgsWithSmsEnabled();  // queries organization_settings
    for (UUID orgId : orgIds) {
        try {
            TenantContext.runAs(orgId, () -> sendForOrg(orgId));
        } catch (Exception e) {
            log.error(\"SMS reminders failed for org {}\", orgId, e);
            // continue to next org — per-org isolation
        }
    }
}

private void sendForOrg(UUID orgId) {
    List<Appointment> tomorrows = appointmentService.getAppointmentsForTomorrow();
    for (Appointment app : tomorrows) {
        try {
            String result = twilioClient.send(...);  // OUTSIDE DB tx
            if (result.indicates_success) {
                markReminderSentInOwnTransaction(app.getId());  // own small tx
            }
        } catch (Exception e) {
            log.warn(\"SMS failed for appointment {}\", app.getId(), e);
            // continue to next appointment — preserve today's failure semantics
        }
    }
}
```

**Key decisions:**
- **`sms_reminders_enabled` lives on `organization_settings`** (V1 schema line 32), NOT on `organizations`. Implement lookup as either a JOIN @Query on OrganizationRepository or a method on OrganizationSettingsRepository.
- **`TenantContext.runAs` per-org**: load-bearing for @TenantId queries inside the loop to see the right tenant.
- **Twilio dispatch OUTSIDE any DB transaction**: no connection held during Twilio I/O and retry backoff sleeps. `markReminderSent` opens its own small tx.
- **Per-org try/catch**: one org's Twilio failure doesn't poison another's batch.
- **Per-appointment try/catch**: preserve today's behavior (one appointment failure doesn't roll back the rest).
- **Twilio creds env-var-sourced**: per-tenant Twilio storage deferred to follow-up branch per `docs/brainstorms/2026-05-24-salon-2-prep-notes.md`. **Salon-2 onboarding is gated by the operator on per-tenant Twilio landing first** — no runtime gate in this file; if a second org with sms_enabled=TRUE appears before per-tenant Twilio exists, it dispatches from salon-1's number. That sequencing is enforced by operator workflow per user's explicit constraint.

### `CrossOrgIsolationIntegrationTest` — PHASE 2 EXIT GATE

Implement the test from S7_RED_BE. This is the AE4 enforcement. Phase 2 does NOT close until this is green.

If a Hibernate quirk with @TenantId on @EmbeddedId surfaces, it surfaces here. Plan calls this the U7 gate: 'any discriminator-on-@EmbeddedId Hibernate quirk surfaces here, one unit before Phase 2 closes.'

### Dependencies

AppointmentService (S7_SVC).

### Verification

- All slice 7 backend tests green.
- `CrossOrgIsolationIntegrationTest` GREEN — Phase 2 exit gate closed.
- Manual: dev SMS scheduled tick (override cron temporarily) dispatches against migrated dataset.

### Considerations

- Cron schedule `0 0 15 * * *` zone `America/New_York` unchanged.
- Twilio short-circuit on `21610` (opted-out) + retry-on-`5xx`/`429` preserved verbatim.
- AGENTS.md: 'Don't talk to Twilio outside SmsService' — preserve.

## Goal

The single chokepoint for all appointment timestamp formatting in the frontend. All `dayjs(...).format(...)` against appointment fields goes through here.

### Files

**`client/src/utils/datetime.ts`** (new):

```ts
import dayjs from 'dayjs'
import utc from 'dayjs/plugin/utc'
import timezone from 'dayjs/plugin/timezone'
dayjs.extend(utc)
dayjs.extend(timezone)

function requireTz(orgTz: string | undefined): asserts orgTz is string {
  if (!orgTz) throw new Error('orgTz is required — never fall back to browser tz')
}

export function formatTime(iso: string, orgTz: string | undefined): string {
  requireTz(orgTz)
  return dayjs(iso).tz(orgTz).format('h:mm A')
}

export function formatDate(iso: string, orgTz: string | undefined): string {
  requireTz(orgTz)
  return dayjs(iso).tz(orgTz).format('dddd, MMMM D, YYYY')
}

export function formatDateTime(iso: string, orgTz: string | undefined): string {
  requireTz(orgTz)
  return dayjs(iso).tz(orgTz).format('MMM D, YYYY h:mm A')
}

export function toIsoFromSalonInput(date: string, time: string, orgTz: string | undefined): string {
  requireTz(orgTz)
  return dayjs.tz(`${date}T${time}`, orgTz).toISOString()
}

export function minutesFromMidnight(iso: string, orgTz: string | undefined): number {
  requireTz(orgTz)
  const d = dayjs(iso).tz(orgTz)
  return d.hour() * 60 + d.minute()
}

export function businessHoursMin(orgTz: string | undefined) {
  requireTz(orgTz)
  const todayInSalonTz = dayjs().tz(orgTz).format('YYYY-MM-DD')
  return dayjs.tz(`${todayInSalonTz}T09:00:00`, orgTz)
}

export function businessHoursMax(orgTz: string | undefined) {
  requireTz(orgTz)
  const todayInSalonTz = dayjs().tz(orgTz).format('YYYY-MM-DD')
  return dayjs.tz(`${todayInSalonTz}T21:00:00`, orgTz)
}
```

### Why fail-fast on undefined orgTz

The plan calls this an invariant: helpers THROW rather than silently fall back to browser tz. The `<RequireMe>` boundary in slice 2 guarantees orgTz is defined before any consumer renders — so a throw here is unreachable in practice. But the throw eliminates the per-component undefined-orgTz handling burden AND prevents a silent regression if `<RequireMe>` is bypassed.

### Why a helper module, not a hook

`useFormatTime()` hook variant was considered. Plain functions are simpler and don't require a re-render coupling. Consumers pass `orgTz` from `useMe()` data at the call site. A later ergonomic hook wrapper can wrap this; not blocking.

### `client/src/types/Appointment.ts` (modify)

- `id: string` (was number).
- `services: string[]` (was number[]).
- Replace `date`, `startTime`, `endTime` with `startsAt: string`, `endsAt: string`.
- Preserve: phone, customerName, employeeId (string), reminderSentAt (string|null), archivedAt (string|null), showedUp (boolean).

### `client/src/api/appointments/appointments.ts` (modify)

- Request/response types match.
- Remove any `+id`/`Number(id)` coercion.

### Dependencies

useMe hook (slice 2). dayjs already installed.

### Verification

- `datetime.test.ts` (S7_RED_FE) goes green.
- `cd client && npx tsc --noEmit` clean.

### Considerations

- AGENTS.md: 'shared primitives go in `client/src/components/`' — but `datetime.ts` is utilities not components, so `client/src/utils/` (matches slice 5's `colors.ts`).
- Don't add a global TZ default (e.g., `dayjs.tz.setDefault('America/New_York')`) — the design is per-call orgTz.

