### `GlobalExceptionHandler.java`

ADD a JPA-side handler ALONGSIDE the existing Mongo `DuplicateKeyException` handler:

```java
@ExceptionHandler(DataIntegrityViolationException.class)
ResponseEntity<Map<String, String>> handleDataIntegrityViolation(DataIntegrityViolationException ex) {
    String description = inferDescription(ex); // e.g., 'A client with that phone number already exists.'
    return ResponseEntity.status(409).body(Map.of("description", description));
